WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:13.820
As an artist,
作为一名艺术家，

2
00:00:13.820 --> 00:00:15.820
connection is very important to me.
联系对我来说是非常重要的 。

3
00:00:15.820 --> 00:00:18.820
Through my work I'm trying to articulate
通过我的艺术作品我试着阐明

4
00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:21.820
that humans are not separate from nature
人类不是与自然分隔开

5
00:00:21.820 --> 00:00:24.820
and that everything is interconnected.
而是每一件事都是互相联系的。

6
00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:27.820
I first went to Antarctica almost 10 years ago,
大约10年前我第一次去了南极洲，

7
00:00:27.820 --> 00:00:29.820
where I saw my first icebergs.
我也第一次看到了冰山。

8
00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:32.820
I was in awe.
我感到敬畏。

9
00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:35.820
My heart beat fast, my head was dizzy,
我的心快速地砰动，头晕目眩，

10
00:00:35.820 --> 00:00:38.820
trying to comprehend what it was that stood in front of me.
试着理解在我面前的这到底是什么。

11
00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:40.820
The icebergs around me
在我身边的冰山

12
00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:43.820
were almost 200 feet out of the water,
浮出水面几乎200英尺。

13
00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:45.820
and I could only help but wonder
我只能感到很奇怪

14
00:00:45.820 --> 00:00:47.820
that this was one snowflake
这就是一片雪花

15
00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:49.820
on top of another snowflake,
覆盖在另一片雪花，

16
00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:51.820
year after year.
年复一年形成的。

17
00:00:51.820 --> 00:00:53.820
Icebergs are born
冰山的形成是

18
00:00:53.820 --> 00:00:56.820
when they calve off of glaciers
当它们从冰川断裂开

19
00:00:56.820 --> 00:00:59.820
or break off of ice shelves.
或者从冰架上断裂开。

20
00:01:01.820 --> 00:01:05.820
Each iceberg has its own individual personality.
每个冰山都有它们自己的独特个性。

21
00:01:05.820 --> 00:01:07.820
They have a distinct way
它们

22
00:01:07.820 --> 00:01:09.820
of interacting with their environment
与其周边的环境

23
00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:12.820
and their experiences.
和其情况的互动具有一个鲜明的方式。

24
00:01:12.820 --> 00:01:14.820
Some refuse to give up
有些冰山拒绝妥协

25
00:01:14.820 --> 00:01:16.820
and hold on to the bitter end,
坚持到底，

26
00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:18.820
while others can't take it anymore
而另一些冰山就不能忍受

27
00:01:18.820 --> 00:01:22.820
and crumble in a fit of dramatic passion.
在一时剧烈激情喷涌下就水崩冰裂。

28
00:01:22.820 --> 00:01:25.820
It's easy to think, when you look at an iceberg,
当你看到冰山，很容易就想到

29
00:01:25.820 --> 00:01:27.820
that they're isolated,
它们都是孤立的，

30
00:01:27.820 --> 00:01:29.820
that they're separate and alone,
它们是独立的，单独一体的，

31
00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:32.820
much like we as humans sometimes view ourselves.
更像是我们人类有时候对自身的看法。

32
00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:34.820
But the reality is far from it.
但现实远不止这个。

33
00:01:34.820 --> 00:01:36.820
As an iceberg melts,
随着冰山融化，

34
00:01:36.820 --> 00:01:38.820
I am breathing in
我呼吸到

35
00:01:38.820 --> 00:01:40.820
its ancient atmosphere.
它古老的气味。

36
00:01:40.820 --> 00:01:42.820
As the iceberg melts,
随着冰山融化，

37
00:01:42.820 --> 00:01:46.820
it is releasing mineral-rich fresh water
它释放了富有矿物质的鲜水

38
00:01:46.820 --> 00:01:49.820
that nourishes many forms of life.
它们滋养了万物。

39
00:01:50.820 --> 00:01:53.820
I approach photographing these icebergs
我着手拍摄这些冰山

40
00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:56.820
as if I'm making portraits of my ancestors,
好似我在拍摄我祖先的肖像，

41
00:01:56.820 --> 00:01:59.820
knowing that in these individual moments
了解到在这些个别的时刻

42
00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:01.820
they exist in that way
冰山原是以那样方式存在

43
00:02:01.820 --> 00:02:03.820
and will never exist that way again.
但再也不会像那样存在了。

44
00:02:03.820 --> 00:02:05.820
It is not a death when they melt;
当它们融化时，这绝不是死亡；

45
00:02:05.820 --> 00:02:07.820
it is not an end,
也绝不是一个终结，

46
00:02:07.820 --> 00:02:09.820
but a continuation
而是

47
00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:12.820
of their path through the cycle of life.
通往生生不息之路的一个延续。

48
00:02:17.820 --> 00:02:21.820
Some of the ice in the icebergs that I photograph is very young --
我拍摄过的冰山，有些冰是非常年轻--

49
00:02:21.820 --> 00:02:23.820
a couple thousand years old.
几千年年龄。

50
00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:25.820
And some of the ice
有些冰

51
00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:28.820
is over 100,000 years old.
超过十万年。

52
00:02:37.820 --> 00:02:39.820
The last pictures I'd like to show you
我想给大家展示的最后图片

53
00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:41.820
are of an iceberg that I photographed
是我在格陵兰岛的

54
00:02:41.820 --> 00:02:44.820
in Qeqetarsuaq, Greenland.
Kekertsuatsiak上拍摄的一个冰山。

55
00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:46.820
It's a very rare occasion
这是一个非常难得的机会

56
00:02:46.820 --> 00:02:48.820
that you get to actually witness
大家实际上得以见证

57
00:02:48.820 --> 00:02:50.820
an iceberg rolling.
一个冰山翻滚。

58
00:02:50.820 --> 00:02:52.820
So here it is.
所以这就如图所示。

59
00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:55.820
You can see on the left side a small boat.
在左边你能看到一个小船。

60
00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:58.820
That's about a 15-foot boat.
这是一个约15英尺的船。

61
00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:00.820
And I'd like you to pay attention
我想让你注意

62
00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:02.820
to the shape of the iceberg
冰山的形状

63
00:03:02.820 --> 00:03:05.820
and where it is at the waterline.
它在水面上的变形。

64
00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:07.820
You can see here, it begins to roll,
在这儿你看到它开始翻滚，

65
00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:09.820
and the boat has moved to the other side, and the man is standing there.
小船移动到另一边，一个男人站在那里。

66
00:03:09.820 --> 00:03:12.820
This is an average-size Greenlandic iceberg.
这是一个平均尺寸的格陵兰冰山。

67
00:03:12.820 --> 00:03:15.820
It's about 120 feet above the water,
它浮出水面大约有120英尺高

68
00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:17.820
or 40 meters.
或者40米高。

69
00:03:17.820 --> 00:03:19.820
And this video is real time.
这视频是实时拍摄的。

70
00:03:19.820 --> 00:03:27.820
(Music)
（音乐）

71
00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:50.820
And just like that,
就像这冰山，

72
00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:53.820
the iceberg shows you a different side of its personality.
它们展示给大家的是其个性的不同方面。

73
00:03:54.820 --> 00:03:56.820
Thank you.
谢谢。

74
00:03:56.820 --> 00:04:00.820
(Applause)
（掌声）